repro_steps: Review linked files/tests/docs for pm-cvwi (Comments shorthand compatibility and docs parity); run linked verification via pm test pm-cvwi --run when available; compare observed behavior with acceptance criteria and capture results in comments.
resolution: "Comments/notes/learnings add semantics are now explicit and safe: ambiguous CSV-like payloads containing non-text keys fall back to literal plain text, while explicit text= / markdown text: / stdin forms remain structured."
expected_result: "Users can distinguish structured and plain add payload paths from command help/docs, and key-like comma payloads no longer silently truncate trailing fragments."
actual_result: "Parser now preserves text=hello,scope:project as plain text for comments/notes/learnings when non-text keys are present; help/docs updated across main/README/AGENTS/PRD; linked cvwi test runs passed (104 + 41 + 16 tests)."
