  "2026-04-01T11:05:50.847Z",codex-agent,Feature created after deep duplicate search over open/in-progress/blocked/search surfaces.
  "2026-04-01T11:18:49.987Z",codex-agent,"Feature evidence: targeted and full test suites pass after implementation; manual validation confirms positional comments, --add compatibility, and conflict-path usage error. Full coverage gate remains globally below repository threshold (98.14/96.57/98.37/97.99)."
  "2026-04-01T11:19:16.550Z",codex-agent,"Validation: user-reported form now succeeds (pm comments <id> \"...\" --author) without too-many-arguments error."
  "2026-04-01T11:20:09.633Z",codex-agent,"Push evidence: commit 765a7de on origin/main contains parser changes, regression coverage, and docs parity updates."
  "2026-04-01T11:21:33.397Z",codex-agent,"Post-push cleanup: adjusted test indentation only in cli.integration.spec.ts and re-ran that integration suite (35/35 pass)."
  "2026-04-07T18:14:15.301Z",codex-agent,"2026-04-07 scope extension: implement create-time --comment plain-text shorthand parity so pm create accepts simple comment text like pm comments --add while retaining deterministic structured key=value parsing and punctuation-safe guidance. Planned files: src/cli/commands/create.ts (+ shared parse helper only if required), tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts, README/PRD/ARCHITECTURE/CHANGELOG."
  "2026-04-07T18:24:04.211Z",codex-agent,"Implementation progress: create --comment now accepts plain-text shorthand by defaulting to a comment seed when structured parsing fails or when single-key colon text is provided (while preserving strict rejection for ambiguous comma key-like fragments such as text=...,scope:...). Added regression coverage in tests/unit/create-command.spec.ts for plain text and colon shorthand plus existing ambiguity guards."
  "2026-04-25T16:54:40.806Z",codex-agent,"Dogfood finding (2026-04-25): comments/notes/learnings --add payloads passed as single CSV-like strings can be interpreted as plain text entries, which is easy to misread as structured parsing. Review parser/doc ergonomics and add explicit examples for unambiguous structured input."
  "2026-04-27T20:09:24.663Z",codex-agent,"Stale-state normalization 2026-04-27: status intentionally remains in_progress. Core acceptance behavior for comments shorthand shipped, but residual follow-up from latest dogfood note remains: clarify CSV-like --add payload ergonomics (structured vs plain-text ambiguity) with explicit docs/help examples and parser guidance before close."
  "2026-04-27T21:16:37.950Z",codex-agent,"Execution start 2026-04-27: addressing dogfood ambiguity where CSV-like --add payloads can be read as plain text for comments/notes/learnings. Scope: improve command help + docs with explicit structured-vs-plain guidance and add regression coverage that codifies fallback behavior."
  "2026-04-27T21:23:37.982Z",codex-agent,"Implementation 2026-04-27: clarified comments/notes/learnings --add semantics across CLI help/docs and fixed parser ambiguity by preserving payload as plain text whenever parsed CSV-like input includes non-text keys (e.g. text=hello,scope:project). Added unit regressions for comments and notes/learnings fallback behavior."
  "2026-04-27T21:27:35.900Z",codex-agent,"Verification 2026-04-27: pm test pm-cvwi --run --progress passed all linked suites (comments+cli+release-readiness: 104 tests; create-command: 41 tests; notes-learnings: 16 tests). Additional targeted rerun for guidance update also passed before linked run. Regression assertions now cover ambiguous CSV-like add payload fallback for comments/notes/learnings."
  "2026-04-27T21:33:16.349Z",codex-agent,"Final handoff 2026-04-27: global gate run after backlog closeout -> pm validate --check-resolution --check-history-drift --json (warn on legacy resolution backlog: 10 items; history drift hash mismatches: pm-r9ei, pm-vhdc), pm normalize --dry-run --json (rule closed_resolution_backfill count=10), pm context --limit 20 (active_items=0)."
  "2026-05-08T22:53:42.687Z",codex-agent,Reusing existing lineage after duplicate check (context/list/search); implementing simplified comments input with stdin/file support and parity updates.
