learnings[3]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-04-01T20:22:39.883Z",codex-agent,metadata-completeness-improves-multi-agent-handoffs
  "2026-04-27T21:27:40.484Z",codex-agent,"For text-entry commands, treating non-text parsed keys as a plain-text fallback avoids silent truncation and keeps user intent explicit while preserving structured text= and markdown text: paths."
  "2026-05-08T23:07:55.328Z",codex-agent,Agent-facing text-entry commands benefit from first-class stdin and file modes because they avoid shell quoting complexity for multiline markdown evidence.
